TITLE: Compiling Reports from Single Source Directory
DESCRIPTION: Ant target that compiles JRXML files from a single source directory. It creates output directories, defines the compilation task, and specifies compilation parameters including validation and Java file retention.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jaspersoft/jasperreports/blob/master/demo/samples/antcompile/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: xml
CODE:
```
<target name="compile1" description="Compiles report designs specified using the &quot;srcdir&quot; in the &lt;jrc&gt; tag." depends="prepare-sample-classpath"> 
  <mkdir dir="./build/reports"/> 
  <taskdef name="jrc" classname="net.sf.jasperreports.ant.JRAntCompileTask"> 
    <classpath refid="sample-classpath"/>
  </taskdef>
  <jrc 
    srcdir="./reports"
    destdir="./build/reports"
    tempdir="./build/reports"
    keepjava="true"
    xmlvalidation="true">
  <classpath refid="sample-classpath"/>
  <include name="**/*.jrxml"/>
  </jrc>
</target>
```

