TITLE: Defining a JavaBean for JasperReports Data Source (Java)
DESCRIPTION: Defines the `CustomBean` class, a simple JavaBean with properties (city, id, name, street) and corresponding getter methods. It includes a constructor for initialization and a `getMe()` method that returns the object instance itself, which can be used for complex field mappings in JasperReports.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jaspersoft/jasperreports/blob/master/demo/samples/datasource/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
public class CustomBean
{
 private String city;
 private Integer id;
 private String name;
 private String street;

 public CustomBean(
  String pcity,
  Integer pid,
  String pname,
  String pstreet
  )
 {
  city = pcity;
  id = pid;
  name = pname;
  street = pstreet;
 }

 public CustomBean getMe()
 {
  return this;
 }

 public String getCity()
 {
  return city;
 }

 public Integer getId()
 {
  return id;
 }

 public String getName()
 {
  return name;
 }

 public String getStreet()
 {
  return street;
 }
}
```

