TITLE: Defining Token Vocabulary for ANTLR Mapping Parser in Java
DESCRIPTION: Defines symbolic token names and their integer values for an ANTLR 2.7.5 mapping parser. No explicit dependencies are required to interpret this file, as it is generally auto-generated by ANTLR from a grammar file (mapping.g), and serves as a lookup for token values by the parser and lexer. The literals include keywords like 'Axis', 'Columns', and operators such as PLUS and STAR. The expected input is the parser/lexer usage of these constants, and the output is accurate token recognition; any modification must be reflected in the corresponding grammar.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jaspersoft/jasperreports/blob/master/ext/olap/src/main/resources/net/sf/jasperreports/olap/mapping/MappingParserTokenTypes.txt#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
// $ANTLR 2.7.5 (20050128): mapping.g -> MappingParserTokenTypes.txt$
MappingParser    // output token vocab name
LITERAL_Axis="Axis"=4
LPAREN=5
RPAREN=6
LITERAL_Columns="Columns"=7
LITERAL_Rows="Rows"=8
LITERAL_Pages="Pages"=9
LITERAL_Chapters="Chapters"=10
LITERAL_Sections="Sections"=11
LITERAL_Data="Data"=12
LITERAL_FormattedData="FormattedData"=13
COMMA=14
QMARK=15
POINT=16
INT=17
MONDRNAME=18
NAME=19
PLUS=20
MINUS=21
STAR=22
WS=23
DIGIT=24
LETTER=25
```

